The paper discusses a framework for processing fast data, which involves handling large volumes of data in real-time. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) sub-category. Additionally, the paper mentions applications in social media and e-commerce, which suggests that it may also belong to the Databases (cs.DB) and Software Engineering (cs.SE) sub-categories. The paper also discusses challenges related to handling large volumes of data, which suggests that it may belong to the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category. Finally, the paper mentions sensor data streams, Twitter Firehose, and Facebook updates, which suggests that it may also belong to the Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-category.
